15. Final Takeaway

Machine Learning works with:

vectors numerically,
but theoretically those vectors come from:
random variables,
probability measures,
underlying random experiments.

This probabilistic viewpoint forms the foundation of:

statistical learning,
generative models,
deep learning,
modern AI.
